'''谷歌大脑'''（{{lang-en|Google Brain}}）是一个[[深度学习|深度学习]]與[[人工智慧|人工智慧]]科研项目团队，其母公司为[[谷歌|谷歌]]。

==历史==
2011年，“谷歌大脑”的雏形起源于一项[[斯坦福大学|斯坦福大学]]与谷歌公司的联合研究项目。谷歌资深专家[[傑夫·迪恩|傑夫·迪恩]]（Jeff Dean）, 研究员格雷科拉多（Greg Corrado）与斯坦福大学知名人工智能教授[[吴恩达|吴恩达]]（Andrew Ng）<ref>{{cite web|title=Google's Large Scale Deep Neural Networks Project|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KELYHjq9Gbs|accessdate=2015-10-25|archive-date=2019-02-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190216070207/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KELYHjq9Gbs|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=ng-dean-blog /><ref name=nyt-cats />是这个小团队的最初三名成员。其中，吴恩达教授更是从2006年就开始尝试用深度学习技巧来解决人工智能领域的问题，这促使他在2011年与迪恩和克拉多联手创造了一个大型深度学习软件平台“DistBelief”<ref>{{cite web|author1=Jeffrey Dean|title=Large Scale Distributed Deep Networks|url=http://papers.nips.cc/paper/4687-large-scale-distributed-deep-networks.pdf|date=December 2012|accessdate=2015-10-25|display-authors=etal|archive-date=2016-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160126084051/http://papers.nips.cc/paper/4687-large-scale-distributed-deep-networks.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref> 。这是一个架构于谷歌云计算平台上的一个服务。

谷歌大脑一开始只是[[Google_X|Google X]]的一个研究项目而已。但因为它惊人的效益和成功，它脱离了Google X成为了谷歌总公司的单独部门。Google X前负责人埃里克泰勒(Eric Teller)曾透露谷歌大脑团队当时赚到的钱超过了整个Google X部门的成本。<ref>{{cite web|author1=Conor Dougherty|title=Astro Teller, Google’s ‘Captain of Moonshots,’ on Making Profits at Google X|url=http://bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2015/02/16/googles-captain-of-moonshots-on-making-profits-at-google-x/|date=2015-02-16|accessdate=2015-10-25|archive-date=2015-10-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151022154103/http://bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2015/02/16/googles-captain-of-moonshots-on-making-profits-at-google-x/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2012年6月，《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》报道了一个由16000台电脑集群组成的人工神经网络通过[[YouTube|YouTube]]上有关于猫的资料自行训练而能够识别出“猫”这一概念。这个系统集群的机理在于模拟人类大脑活动。<ref name=nyt-cats>{{cite web|url = http://www.nytimes.com/2012/06/26/technology/in-a-big-network-of-computers-evidence-of-machine-learning.html?pagewanted=all|title = How Many Computers to Identify a Cat? 16,000|last = Markoff|first = John|authorlink = John Markoff|date = 2012-06-25|accessdate = 2014-02-11|publisher = ''[[New_York_Times|New York Times]]''|archive-date = 2014-01-24|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140124130041/http://www.nytimes.com/2012/06/26/technology/in-a-big-network-of-computers-evidence-of-machine-learning.html?pagewanted=all|dead-url = no}}</ref>当时这个突破同时被美国国家公共广播<ref name=npr-cats>{{cite web|url = http://www.npr.org/2012/06/26/155792609/a-massive-google-network-learns-to-identify|title = A Massive Google Network Learns To Identify — Cats|publisher = [[National_Public_Radio|National Public Radio]]|date = 2012-06-26|accessdate = 2014-02-11|archive-date = 2014-02-22|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140222012348/http://www.npr.org/2012/06/26/155792609/a-massive-google-network-learns-to-identify|dead-url = no}}</ref>和智慧星球媒体<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.smartplanet.com/blog/science-scope/google-brain-simulator-teaches-itself-to-recognize-cats/|title = Google brain simulator teaches itself to recognize cats|last = Shin|first = Laura|date = 2012-06-26|accessdate = 2014-02-11|publisher = [[SmartPlanet|SmartPlanet]]|archive-date = 2014-02-22|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140222025525/http://www.smartplanet.com/blog/science-scope/google-brain-simulator-teaches-itself-to-recognize-cats/|dead-url = no}}</ref>报道。

2013年3月，谷歌聘用了深度学习领域里的资深专家杰弗里金盾(Geoffrey Hinton)，并收购了他所领导的DNNResearch Inc. 公司。金盾表示他将会将自己的精力分成两部分，同时着重大学里的科研和在谷歌的工作。<ref>{{cite press release|title=U of T neural networks start-up acquired by Google|date=2013-03-12|location=Toronto, ON|url=http://media.utoronto.ca/media-releases/u-of-t-neural-networks-start-up-acquired-by-google/|accessdate=2013-03-13|archive-date=2019-10-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191008004030/https://media.utoronto.ca/media-releases/u-of-t-neural-networks-start-up-acquired-by-google/|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

2014年1月26日，多家媒体机构报道谷歌以未公布的价格并购了英國[[DeepMind|DeepMind]]科技公司。有分析师后来描述这次收购耗费了谷歌400万英镑（650万美金），虽然同有线报表明这次收购价值500万英镑。<ref name=technologyreview-deepmind>{{cite web|url = http://www.technologyreview.com/news/524026/is-google-cornering-the-market-on-deep-learning/|title = Is Google Cornering the Market on Deep Learning? A cutting-edge corner of science is being wooed by Silicon Valley, to the dismay of some academics.|last = Regalado|first = Antonio|date = 2014-01-29|accessdate = 2014-02-11|publisher = [[Technology_Review|Technology Review]]|archive-date = 2015-11-27|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20151127145500/http://www.technologyreview.com/news/524026/is-google-cornering-the-market-on-deep-learning/|dead-url = no}}</ref><ref name=wired-2014>{{cite web|url = http://www.wired.com/business/2014/01/google-buying-way-making-brain-irrelevant/|title = Google’s Grand Plan to Make Your Brain Irrelevant|last = Wohlsen|first = Marcus|date = 2014-01-27|accessdate = 2014-02-11|publisher = ''[[Wired_Magazine|Wired Magazine]]''|archive-date = 2014-02-08|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140208012915/http://www.wired.com/business/2014/01/google-buying-way-making-brain-irrelevant/|dead-url = no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Google Acquires UK AI startup Deepmind|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2014/jan/27/google-acquires-uk-artificial-intelligence-startup-deepmind|publisher=The Guardian|accessdate=2014-01-27|archive-date=2014-02-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140203164210/http://www.theguardian.com/technology/2014/jan/27/google-acquires-uk-artificial-intelligence-startup-deepmind|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Report of Acquisition, TechCrunch|url=http://techcrunch.com/2014/01/26/google-deepmind/|publisher=TechCrunch|accessdate=2014-01-27|archive-date=2014-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140127114318/http://techcrunch.com/2014/01/26/google-deepmind/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Reuters Report|last=Oreskovic|first=Alexei|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/01/27/us-google-deepmind-idUSBREA0Q03220140127|publisher=Reuters|accessdate=2014-01-27|archive-date=2014-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140127042513/http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/01/27/us-google-deepmind-idUSBREA0Q03220140127|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Google Acquires Artificial Intelligence Start-Up DeepMind|url=http://www.theverge.com/2014/1/26/5348640/google-deepmind-acquisition-robotics-ai|publisher=The Verge|accessdate=2014-01-27|archive-date=2017-01-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170104105853/http://www.theverge.com/2014/1/26/5348640/google-deepmind-acquisition-robotics-ai|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Google acquires AI pioneer DeepMind Technologies|url=http://arstechnica.com/business/2014/01/google-acquires-ai-pioneer-deepmind-technologies/|publisher=Ars Technica|accessdate=2014-01-27|archive-date=2014-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140130040807/http://arstechnica.com/business/2014/01/google-acquires-ai-pioneer-deepmind-technologies/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 这次收购发生在Facebook公司与DeepMind交涉许久无果的情况下。<ref>{{cite web|title=Google beats Facebook for Acquisition of DeepMind Technologies|url=https://www.theinformation.com/Google-beat-Facebook-For-DeepMind-Creates-Ethics-Board|accessdate=2014-01-27|archive-date=2014-01-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140131121719/https://www.theinformation.com/Google-beat-Facebook-For-DeepMind-Creates-Ethics-Board|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==在谷歌产品中的运用==
目前谷歌大脑的技术主要运用于[[Android|安卓操作系统]]里的[[语音识别|语音识别]]控件中<ref>{{cite web|url=http://googleresearch.blogspot.com/2012/08/speech-recognition-and-deep-learning.html|title=Speech Recognition and Deep Learning|publisher=[[Google|Google]]|work=Google Research Blog|date=2012-08-06|accessdate=2014-02-11|archive-date=2014-03-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140306214255/http://googleresearch.blogspot.com/2012/08/speech-recognition-and-deep-learning.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，同时也用于谷歌社交平台[[Google+|Google+]]里的图片搜索功能<ref>{{cite web|url=http://googleresearch.blogspot.com/2013/06/improving-photo-search-step-across.html|title=Improving Photo Search: A Step Across the Semantic Gap|publisher=[[Google|Google]]|work=Google Research Blog|date=2013-06-12|accessdate=2017-02-10|archive-date=2016-03-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160327163728/http://googleresearch.blogspot.com/2013/06/improving-photo-search-step-across.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，而且也对谷歌的智能视频推荐起到了至关重要的作用。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://time.com/3882422/google-youtube/|title=This Is Google’s Plan to Save YouTube|work=[[Time_(magazine)|Time]]|date=2015-05-18|accessdate=2017-02-10|archive-date=2016-09-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160910181846/http://time.com/3882422/google-youtube/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

谷歌大脑一开始是由谷歌资深研究人员杰夫迪恩和斯坦福教授吴恩达组成的<ref name=ng-dean-blog>{{cite web|author1=Jeff Dean and Andrew Ng|title=Using large-scale brain simulations for machine learning and A.I.|url=http://googleblog.blogspot.com/2012/06/using-large-scale-brain-simulations-for.html|website=Official Google Blog|accessdate=2015-01-26|date=2012-06-26|archive-date=2015-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150206054621/http://googleblog.blogspot.com/2012/06/using-large-scale-brain-simulations-for.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>（吴恩达后来加入了[[百度|百度]]的人工智能事业部<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scmp.com/news/china/article/1519211/ex-google-brain-head-andrew-ng-lead-baidus-artificial-intelligence-drive|title=Ex-Google Brain head Andrew Ng to lead Baidu's artificial intelligence drive|publisher=[[South_China_Morning_Post|South China Morning Post]]|accessdate=2017-02-10|archive-date=2017-01-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170114123720/http://www.scmp.com/news/china/article/1519211/ex-google-brain-head-andrew-ng-lead-baidus-artificial-intelligence-drive|dead-url=no}}</ref>）。截止2014年，这个团队的成员有杰夫迪恩、杰弗里金盾、格雷柯拉多，阔克乐(Quoc Le)，伊亚萨茨科沃(Iiya Sutskever)，亚力克斯克里哲福斯基(Alex Krizhevsky)，萨米本吉(Samy Bengio)和文森特万浩科(Vincent Vanhoucke)。目前，谷歌大脑团队有多名中国人或华裔在职。

==研究方向==
谷歌大脑团队的标语为“让机器更智能，以提升人类生活质量。” 其七个主要研究方向如下：机器学习算法和技术、医疗健康、机器学习支撑电脑系统、机器人、自然语言理解、音乐和艺术创作、[[知觉仿真|知觉仿真]]。

其团队相信知识应该为全人类共享，所以其所有科研成果都会公开发表。<ref>{{cite web|title=Research at Google|url=https://research.google.com/teams/brain|website=Google Brain Team|accessdate=2017-02-10|archive-date=2017-02-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170210150403/https://research.google.com/teams/brain/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

